The paper addresses the topic of reading comprehension, which is a subfield of natural language processing (NLP) and machine learning. The paper investigates popular benchmarks for reading comprehension and establishes baselines for their difficulty. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language), which focuses on NLP and its intersection with computer science. Other likely sub-categories include cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.IR (Information Retrieval), and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing), which are all relevant to the topic of machine learning and NLP.
